The unidentified man allegedly got on the train at Githurai area in Nairobi. [Courtesy]  A man is nursing serious injuries at Maragua District Hospital after jumping off a moving cargo train in Maragua Ridge area.  The unidentified man allegedly got on the train at Githurai area in Nairobi as he could not afford fare to his native Murang’a County.  Fearing arrest at Kandundu Railway Station near Murang’a town for boarding the train illegally, the man allegedly jumped off at Mbombo area.  Confirming the incident, Maragua sub-county police commander Alexander Shikondi said the victim was rushed to the hospital and will record a statement once he recovers. "We are yet to get information from the train crew as well as the station manager at Maragua," said Shikondi.   More to follow...  By Kamau Muthoni | 1 day ago By Elvince Joshua | 2 days ago By Ndungu Gachane | 3 days ago By Mose Sammy | 3 days ago Enjoy unlimited access to The Standard website at a 50% discount on the yearly plan.